      <div id="briefs-container"><div class="briefs-item"><a href="http://news.byu.edu/archive12-aug-honors.aspx" title=""><img alt="Head and shoulders of Michael Pinegar" src="http://home.byu.edu/home/sites/default/files/pinegar.jpg"></a><h3><a href="http://news.byu.edu/archive12-aug-honors.aspx" title="">Outstanding faculty, staff honored at annual conference</a></h3></div><div class="briefs-item"><a href="http://www.provo4students.org/" title=""><img alt="Image of downtown Center Street" src="http://home.byu.edu/home/sites/default/files/Provo-downtown.jpg"></a><h3><a href="http://www.provo4students.org/" title="">New to Provo? Check out the student guide to the city</a></h3></div><div class="briefs-item omega"><a href="http://universe.byu.edu/index.php/2012/08/21/president-samuelson-boosts-faculty/" title=""><img alt="Head and shoulders of Cecil O. Samuelson" src="http://home.byu.edu/home/sites/default/files/samuelson-l.jpg"></a><h3><a href="http://universe.byu.edu/index.php/2012/08/21/president-samuelson-boosts-faculty/" title="">BYU's prophetically-chartered course will never change</a></h3></div></div>      <div id="news-container"><div class="news-item"><a href="http://youtu.be/C3r1SNht2fM?hd=1" title=""><img alt="home construction site in the desert of Bluff, Utah" src="http://home.byu.edu/home/sites/default/files/Bluff-utah.jpg"></a><h3><a href="http://youtu.be/C3r1SNht2fM?hd=1" title="">A summer of service</a></h3><p>BYU&#39;s Global Engineering Outreach (GEO) Club recently worked with other partners to help construct homes for Navajo families in Bluff, Utah. <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C3r1SNht2fM">Watch them</a> go forth to serve.</p>
</div><div class="news-item omega"><a href="http://news.byu.edu/archive12-aug-workplacehealth.aspx" title=""><img alt="A worker lays back in his office chair surrounded by junk food" src="http://home.byu.edu/home/sites/default/files/habits.jpg"></a><h3><a href="http://news.byu.edu/archive12-aug-workplacehealth.aspx" title="">Poor employee health means slacking on the job, business losses</a></h3><p>Expanding employee waistlines could be shrinking company bottom lines, new research shows. A study led by BYU health science professor Ray Merrill finds that employees with unhealthy habits are causing substantially higher levels of lost workplace productivity. <a href="http://news.byu.edu/archive12-aug-workplacehealth.aspx">See what Merrill says about &quot;presenteeism</a>.&quot;</p>
</div></div>
